==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[FreeGrid_Sketch|FreeGrid Sketch]] tool generates an inner box profile sketch.

<!--T:5-->
This tool is part of the [[FreeGrid_Workbench|FreeGrid Workbench]], an [https://www.freecad.org/addons.php external workbench] that can be installed with the [[Image:Std_AddonMgr.svg|24px]] [[Std_AddonMgr|Addon Manager]].

==Usage== <!--T:6-->

<!--T:7-->
# Optionally select an existing [[FreeGrid_StorageBox|storage box]].
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:FreeGrid_Sketch.svg|16px]] [[FreeGrid_Sketch|Sketch]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|FreeGrid → [[Image:FreeGrid_Sketch.svg|16px]] Sketch}} option from the menu.
# If no box has been selected:
## The '''Sketch size''' task panel opens.
## Specify the '''Width''' and '''Depth''' in terms of 50mm units.
## Optionally check the '''Include open front''' checkbox to create a sketch for an open box.
## Press the {{Button|OK}} button.
# A sketch is created.


